WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:29.940
🎵Music play🎵

00:30.000 --> 00:39.160
Welcome to week two of six week renew groundwork session. So we're gonna start

00:39.160 --> 00:45.960
on the lunge. This horse is very quiet on the lunge so it is in a halter. It's

00:45.960 --> 00:52.320
also very sensitive on its face to my aides and cues so if your horse is

00:52.320 --> 00:57.680
anything less than that then it's a good idea to do this exercise or these

00:57.680 --> 01:06.800
exercises in a bridle and if your horse is very distracted then also with

01:06.800 --> 01:12.280
side reins and a surcingle so that they can remain straight and do a little bit

01:12.280 --> 01:20.440
more focused work. This horse is very focused on its own. So already what we

01:20.440 --> 01:25.440
want to get from this exercise is being able to control the horse's step with

01:25.440 --> 01:34.360
your breath. So as I inhale there she opens her step in the walk and makes it

01:34.360 --> 01:43.160
bigger and as I come closer smaller with my body she's gonna make it smaller. So

01:43.160 --> 01:52.680
both my arms are representing that being very obvious with the step. Making sure

01:52.760 --> 01:58.000
that you're going both ways I like to switch at the walk, switch at the trot

01:58.000 --> 02:04.120
and switch at the canter as opposed to doing all walk trot canter one direction

02:04.120 --> 02:09.760
and then changing direction. I like to give them a well-rounded warm-up or just

02:09.760 --> 02:18.160
integrate into the exercise. So in order to track how large the horse's step is

02:18.200 --> 02:25.040
you watch where the front foot is falling and the hind foot is going to

02:25.040 --> 02:32.920
either step into it behind it or in front of it. So we have two views here

02:32.920 --> 02:39.120
one is going to be your view in the trot from the center of the circle and as you

02:39.120 --> 02:44.680
can see when I open my body and get bigger and wider with my body she's

02:44.680 --> 02:49.720
going to open her step up and when I get smaller with my body she's going to

02:49.720 --> 02:59.840
close her step so making it shorter. So in order to get this task accomplished

02:59.840 --> 03:05.440
with the horses you have to be very sensitive in your person and make them

03:05.440 --> 03:13.560
attentive. So as you can see there as we zoom in my body is getting smaller there

03:13.600 --> 03:19.860
arms are coming closer to the body chest is coming narrower and the step is

03:19.860 --> 03:26.760
getting smaller and as I raise up bigger and wider even the whip can raise if you

03:26.760 --> 03:35.000
need to opening the body then the step opens up. The same exercise in the canter

03:35.000 --> 03:40.600
as in the walk and the trot as you open your body and make it bigger the horse

03:40.640 --> 03:45.440
is going to have a step bigger and as you close your body and make it smaller

03:45.440 --> 03:51.640
or hold the contraction then they're going to make their steps smaller. So

03:51.640 --> 03:58.200
like I said this is the most attentive horse. If your horse is less attentive

03:58.200 --> 04:05.800
then it's important to make your aids more clear and more obvious to them so

04:05.840 --> 04:12.200
they can learn it. And you may need to correct them if they have limited

04:12.200 --> 04:15.360
lunging abilities.

04:22.560 --> 04:29.040
So there you can really see how the opening of the body is very obvious.

04:29.880 --> 04:38.040
When we get to this view you can see the step clearly getting bigger and then

04:38.040 --> 04:47.160
smaller and then bigger by the way she holds her back and the physical length

04:47.160 --> 04:50.000
of her step.

